<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN FOUND SHOT TO DEATH IN SANTEE GARAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man was found shot to death Monday in a garage in Santee, and 
San Diego County Sheriff's Department investigators were questioning three 
residents at the house. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Kim Carson said deputies were called to the home in the 10100 block of 
Magnolia Avenue about 7 a.m. by one of the residents, who dialed 911 and 
reported a shooting at that location. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies found a dead man in the garage, apparently the victim of a gunshot. 
His identity was not released Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said three occupants of the house were removed for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
"It is believed one of the occupants may have fired the weapon, but the 
circumstances around the shooting are not yet known," Carson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
