Foreign Film Entries: The largest number of entries for the best 
foreign-language film award since the category was established in 1956 have 
been received for the 62nd annual Academy Awards, Oscar officials said. In all, 
37 countries submitted foreign entries, which are also eligible to compete in 
other Oscar categories provided they meet the requirements. The Oscars 
ceremonies will be telecast live on ABC from the Music Center on March 26. 
