<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PALMDALE FIRE CAUSES $850,000 DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire at a two-story commercial building in Palmdale early Monday caused 
$850,000 in damage before it was controlled by Los Angeles County firefighters, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze broke out about 12:40 a.m. on the second floor of the Pyramid Square 
building in the 38400 block of 9th Street East, spokesman Randy Orr said. 
</P>
<P>
It took about 50 firefighters 40 minutes to extinguish the blaze, Orr said. No 
injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
Damage was estimated at $600,000 to the structure and $250,000 to the contents, 
Orr said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
