<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BAKERSFIELD; 
</P>
<P>
DRUNK DRIVING SUSPECT FATALLY SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drunk driver was shot to death in his driveway by California 
Highway Patrol officers when he fired an assault rifle at them, officials said. 
Officers Brian Smith and Tom Sayles tried to stop Mark Ivey, 28, as he drove 
eastbound on Casa Loma Drive about 1:15 a.m., CHP dispatcher Linda Stevens 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Ivey did not stop his pickup truck, so the officers pursued him until he 
stopped in his driveway in the Rexland Acres area, Stevens said. As Officers 
Ken Perez and Victor Lacey arrived to join Smith and Sayles, Ivey pulled out an 
assault rifle resembling an Uzi and fired at least one round at the officers, 
Stevens said. All four of the officers returned fire. 
</P>
