<P>
AMERICAN, NICARAGUA NUN KILLED IN ATTACK BY U.S.-BACKED REBELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANAGUA, Nicaragua 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two nuns, one an American, were killed today in an attack by U.S.-backed Contra 
rebels in northeast Nicaragua, the official Voice of Nicaragua radio said. 
</P>
<P>
The radio identified the American nun as Maureen Courtrier and the Nicaraguan 
nun as Teresa Rosales. 
</P>
<P>
American priest Paul Smith, an auxiliary bishop in Bluefields, Marcelino 
Estrada, a Nicaraguan priest and Francisca Colomer, a nun were also wounded. 
</P>
<P>
The group was attacked in their car as they traveled this morning between the 
towns of Cabezas and Mina Rosita. 
</P>
</TEXT>
