<P>
DU PONT TO SELL VIROLOGY UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WILMINGTON, Del. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Du Pont Co. said today it will sell its virology blood-screening business to 
Johnson &amp; Johnson and Chiron Corp. for undisclosed terms. 
</P>
<P>
Du Pont, the nation's No. 1 chemical company, said, "The sale is the first step 
in a strategy calling for increased spending in (our) core diagnostics business 
while divesting some non-strategic diagnostic product lines developed or 
acquired in recent years." 
</P>
<P>
The blood-screening business to be sold includes certain kits that detect the 
presence of acquired immune deficiency syndrome and other diseases in donated 
blood. 
</P>
