<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TANGO' DANCES TO TOP AS BOX OFFICE REBOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NINA J. EASTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Christmas box-office blues are over, with most of the season's top movies 
enjoying a huge leap in business during the New Year's Day weekend. 
</P>
<P>
"Tango &amp; Cash," Warner's Sylvester Stallone-Kurt Russell buddy movie, moved 
up 53% to top the chart with about $10.4 million, according to preliminary 
figures released today. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Danny De Vito's black comedy about divorce, "War of the Roses," 
jumped more than 140%, with roughly $10 million worth of tickets sold over the 
four-day weekend. And children flocked to see Disney's animated feature, "The 
Little Mermaid." 
</P>
<P>
Its early business may have been disappointing -- particularly considering the 
critical acclaim surrounding the old-fashioned fairy tale -- but ticket sales 
jumped nearly 200% over the weekend to nearly $10 million. 
</P>
<P>
Universal's "Back to the Future II," which opened more than a month ago, also 
made a big comeback with more than $8 million in ticket sales, a 100% increase 
over the Christmas weekend. NINA J. EASTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
